refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public mysql_xdevapi\CollectionModifymysql_xdevapi\CollectionModify::sort stringsort_expr
Sort the result set by the field that has been selected in in the sort_expr argument, the allowed orders are: 1) ASC: Ascending. 2) DESC: Descending. This operation is equivalent to the 'ORDER BY' SQL operation and it follows the same set of rules for what concerns the ordering option.
&warn.undocumented.func;

&reftitle.parameters;
sort_expr
One or more sorting expression can be provided, the evaluation of these will be from the leftmost to the rightmost, each expression must be separated by a comma.
